      "en": {
        "purpose": "To screen for ASD (Autism Spectrum Disorder) in adult psychiatric outpatients by using a 14 item self-evaluation questionnaire.To calculate the total score for the RAADS-14 self-evaluation questionnaire and to give a clinical meaning to the score´s total value.",
        "keywords": [
          "autism",
          "psychiatry",
          "ASD",
          "RAADS-14",
          "patient questionnaire"
        ],
        "use": "To be used in adult psychiatric outpatients. This is a shorten version of the 80 item Ritvo Autism and Asperger Diagnostic Scale-Revised (RAADS-R). The score range from a minimum of 0 to a maximum of 42. Three main subdomains are included: Mentalizing deficits, Social anxiety and Sensory reactivity.Three scoring categories are possible:31 \u0026 up Autism found; 14 – 30 Autism likely; 0 – 13 No autism symptoms.",
        "misuse": "Do not use for children or teens, do not use to calculate other score than the total score for the RAADS-14 self-evaluation questionnaire.Do not use for other than to screen adult psychiatric outpatients for ASD. Do not use to register results for the 80 points RAADS score."
      }
